      <p>Bagdatbay Ismailov told Elena Urlaeva that during the Soviet era the Karakalpak Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic had been an economically developed region; Karakalpaks were engaged in agriculture; every district and every state farm had many poultry farms and livestock farms; high‑breed cows produced plenty of milk; agriculture was well developed and had abundant machinery; tractor drivers and milkmaids received awards in Moscow; workers rested for free in sanatoriums; no one was sick; and food was good."</p>
