      <p>Zhumabay fled to Kazakhstan and then to Kyrgyzstan seeking asylum, but his request was denied. Zhumabay Sagidullaev was subsequently placed on a wanted list. While Zhumabay was in Kyrgyzstan, his farm was looted. On May 24, 2015, a confiscation act for the livestock was drawn up by court executor Sh. G. Imalatdinov, though the document significantly underreported the actual number of animals. The act was also signed by district police officer D. Aibusynov, shirkat director Urman Kozhanov, and veterinarian K. Zhabbarov. On July 1, 2022, Judge D. Srazhatdinov of the Takhtakupyr Criminal Court issued a ruling based on Article 84: "Grounds for terminating a criminal case without deciding the issue of guilt."</p>
